title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>An element <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[u]]></fr:tex> of a <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-001S.xml"
addr="jms-001S"
title="Pointed dcpo">pointed</fr:link> dpco <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is called <fr:em>positive</fr:em> when for any semidirected subset <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[I\subseteq  A]]></fr:tex>, if <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[u\sqsubseteq  \bigsqcup {I}]]></fr:tex> then <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[I]]></fr:tex> is inhabited. We will write <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {pos}\,{u}]]></fr:tex> to mean that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[u]]></fr:tex> is a positive element.</fr:p><fr:p>(This is adapted from <fr:link
type="local"
